description: From Latin ēmānāre (“to flow out, spring out of, arise, proceed from”), from e (“out”) + mānāre (“to flow”).

verbs.description: emanate (third-person singular simple present emanates, present participle emanating, simple past and past participle emanated)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To come from a source; issue from.
(transitive, rare) To send or give out; manifest.
